item.title: © Staff of the red Star [nope.]
item.dc:creator: @dylan_0789 dylan_0789
item.description:
@dylan_0789 wrote:

[quote=“rip4d, post:4, topic:398678”]The rest of the staff has plenty of room for detail, don’t exclude it

The concept is nice, but the model (or at least the lighting…) was kinda meh. The prongs are off center, and the rendered polygons in it are awkwardly colored (probably a lighting issue, but they seem as if some are raised while others aren’t, making an undesirable effect). My advice, try some other rendering program, haha. Its hard to see detail in the model when the lighting makes it look crappy. Its a decent job, but more time could definitely have been put into it for some fine tuning and what not.[/quote]
Its not the lighting, its his mesh. A cleaner wireframe helps prevent the uneven looking edges. Or, he could hit “set smooth” which renders the model with ‘soft’ edges. (not the same as subsurfacing)

Read full topic
